Từ điển Anh - Việt
◘[rait]
*danh từ
 ■(từ hiếm,nghĩa hiếm) thợ, người làm
 ⁃the wheel must go to the wright for repair
 cái bánh xe cần phải đưa cho thợ chữa

Anh - Anh
wright
■ noun archaic (except in combination) a maker or builder: playwright|shipwright.
Origin
OE wryhta, wyrhta, of W. Gmc origin; related to work.

sentences.en: The Curtiss-Wright plant was running at capacity, so even that aircraft was in short supply.

sentences.en: The Wright brothers had made use of the knowledge of many people before them.

sentences.vi: Winterburn chuyền bóng cho Wright để cầu thủ này đá bóng vào lưới dẫn đến tỷ số 3-1.

sentences.en: She refused to reveal when the adulterous affair started or how she met Wright.

sentences.en: Oh, and miss Wright tell, Chris to photocopy the Director's report.
sentences.vi: Cô wright này, cô bảo chris chụp bản sao tờ báo cáo của giám đốc nhé.

sentences.en: To prove his point, Wright his superb skyscraper for the Johnson Wax Company at Racine, Wisconsin.

sentences.en: The lead author, Dr Rosalind Wright, believes that attitude somehow strengthens the Immune system .
sentences.vi: Người đứng đầu, tiến sĩ Rosalind Wright, tin rằng bằng cách nào đó thái độ đã tăng cường Hệ thống miễn dịch .
